#eNCA #DStv403  JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng Basic Education Panyaza Lesufi believes the three deceased brothers may have been deliberately poisoned by their father. He says the father also attempted suicide. Lesufi expressed his sadness at the tragic deaths of three siblings at Ratanda Primary and Khanya Lesedi Secondary Schools in Ratanda. WATCH | 3 brothers dead, one in hospital after drinking energy drinks The brothers, aged 6, 13, and 16, died on Thursday after their father gave his five children energy drinks while they were preparing for school. Two of the boys died on school premises while the third died on his way to the hospital. A fourth brother is in critical condition at a local hospital. The fifth brother did not consume the energy drink and is fine. Police are investigating the circumstances surrounding their deaths. Watch the full interview with Gauteng Basic Education MEC Panyaza Lesufi below.  #eNCA #DStv403